## SOLVENTS ##
# TIP3P -  Jorgensen, William L., et al. J Chem Phys (1983) + Neria, Eyal, et al. J Chem Phys (1996) + Chen, Alan A., et al. J Phys Chem B (2007)
# TIP4PEW - Horn, Hans W., et al. J Chem Phys (2004)
# FB3/FB4 - Wang, Lee-Ping, et al. J Phys Chem B (2014)
# SPCE - Berendsen, HJC., et al. J Phys Chem (1987)
# SPCEB - Takemura, Kazuhiro and Kitao, Akio. J Phys Chem B (2012)
# OPC -  Izadi, Saeed, et al. J Phys Chem Lett (2014)


Topology/Parameter str files included:
 1. tip3p_ions.str
 2. tip4pew_ions.str
 3. fb3_ions.str
 4. fb4_ions.str
 5. spce_ions.str
 6. spceb_ions.str
 7. opc_ions.str
 
Additionally, included in solvate_boxes are PSF/PDB of equilibrated water boxes for each model:
 1. solvate_boxes/tip3p.(psf/pdb)
 2. solvate_boxes/tip4pew.(psf/pdb)
 3. solvate_boxes/fb3.(psf/pdb)
 4. solvate_boxes/fb4.(psf/pdb)
 5. solvate_boxes/spce.(psf/pdb)
 6. solvate_boxes/spceb.(psf/pdb)
 7. solvate_boxes/opc.(psf/pdb)

SOLVATE USAGE:

To solvate a system with AMBERff using water model $MODEL, in addition to standard arguments ($args)
include the following flags for solvating with non-standard solvent:

	package require sovate
  	solvate $args -spsf /path/to/solvate_boxes/$MODEL.psf -spdb /path/to/solvate_boxes/$MODEL.pdb -stop /path/to/${MODEL}_ions.str -ks "name O"

Alternatively, use AMBERSOLVATE package.

AMBERSOLVATE:

AMBERSOLVATE is a wrapper package for SOLVATE for solvating systems with AMBERff water models. It takes all standard
solvate arguments excluding those related to non-standard solvent and an additional -model flag to specify the model:

	package require ambersolvate
	ambersolvate $args -model $MODEL

  Possible $MODEL values include:
   1. tip3p (default)
   2. tip4pew
   3. fb3
   4. fb4
   5. spce
   6. spceb
   7. opc
	